cs.cscollections.lists
Interface ListADT<T>

All Known Subinterfaces:
OrderedListADT<T>, UnorderedListADT<T>
All Known Implementing Classes:
BasicList, OrderedList, UnorderedList
public interface ListADT<T>

The ListADT provides a common interface for list collections.

Version:
v 1.0 3.2016
Author:
S. Sigman

Method Detail

first

T first()

first returns the first element in the list. The list is not modified. It is an error to attempt to access the frist element of an empty list. If the list is empty and the element is not found, an exception is raised.

Throws:
EmptyCollectionException, - ElementNotFoundException

getIth

T getIth(int i)

The getIth method returns the ith element in the list. It is an error to attempt to access an index out of the range 0 .. size()-1.

Parameters:
The - index of the element to return.
Returns:
The element at the specified position in the list.
Throws:
EmptyCollectionException, - ArrayOutOfBoundsException

isEmpty

boolean isEmpty()

isEmpty report if the list is empty or not.

Returns:
True is returned if the list is empty. Otherwise, false is returned.

iterator

java.util.Iterator<T> iterator()

iterator returns an iterator that may be used to traverse the list from first to last.

Returns:
An iterator to the list.

last

T last()

last returns the last emement in the list. The element is not removed from the list. It is an error to attempt to remove the last element from an empty list.

Throws:
EmptyCollectionException

remove

T remove(int pos)

Removes the element in position i in the list. The first element in the list is in position 0. If the element is not found, null is returned. Position must be in the range 0 <= pos < n, where n is the size of the list.

Parameters:
The - index of the element to remove.
Returns:
The element removed or null if not found.
Throws:
@throws - EmptyCollectionException, IndexOutOfBoundsException

remove

T remove(T ele)

Removes the first occurence of the specified element from the list. Removal is on the element's value; not on object identiy.

Parameters:
The - element value to remove.
Returns:
The element removed or null if not found.
Throws:
EmptyCollectionException

removeFirst

T removeFirst()

Removes the first or head element of the collection.

Returns:
The first(head) element in the collection.

removeLast

T removeLast()

Removes the last or tail element of the collection.

Returns:
The last(tail) element in the collection.

size

int size()

size returns the count of elements in the list.

Returns:
The number of elements in the list.

toString

java.lang.String toString()

toString returns the list encoded as a String. Note that type T must provide a toString method.

Overrides:
toString in class java.lang.Object
Returns:
A string encoding of the list.
